1 (iv) When necessary to monitor or manage a student's health care; or
2 (v) When determined appropriate by the school board or otherwise
3 allowed by an appropriate school employee.
4 (3) This section should not be interpreted to authorize monitoring,
5 collecting, or otherwise accessing any information on an electronic
6 communicating device not owned by or provided for academic use by the
7 school district.
8 Sec. 2. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
9 passed and approved according to law.
